# Admin dashboard — UI rules

**Scope:** These rules apply to **`apps/admin-dashboard/`** only. Backend logging and headers follow `master.mdc`, `logger_setup.mdc`, and `header.template.mdc`.

**Stack:** Vite, React 19, TypeScript strict, **TanStack React Query**, **React Router**. No Next.js unless the app is migrated.

---

## 01 — Project layout

Prefer feature-oriented folders under `src/`:

```
apps/admin-dashboard/src/
  components/     # shared UI (presentational)
  contexts/       # React context providers
  lib/            # api-client, types, utilities
  pages/          # route-level screens (PascalCase)
  providers/      # QueryClientProvider, etc.
  assets/         # static images
  App.tsx         # routes / layout shell
  main.tsx        # bootstrap
```

Add `hooks/` when custom hooks grow beyond one-off use in pages.

---

## 02 — Components & files

- **Pages and shared UI:** `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g. `OverviewPage.tsx`).
- **Utilities and API helpers:** `kebab-case.ts` (e.g. `api-client.ts`).
- Prefer **composition**; keep route components thin — data loading in hooks or route loaders + React Query.
- Exported components: include the **canonical JSDoc header** from `.cursor/rules/header.template.mdc`.
- Accept `className` and spread sensible DOM props where it improves reuse; add `data-testid` for critical flows when you add E2E tests.

---

## 03 — Styling

- Global styles: `index.css`, `App.css`. Prefer **CSS modules** or a single design token approach if the app grows; avoid inline style sprawl for layout systems.
- Support **light/dark** if the product requires it (class on `document.documentElement` or a small theme hook).
- Respect **`prefers-reduced-motion`** for any animation you add.

---

## 04 — Data & API

- Use **`@tanstack/react-query`** for server state: queries/mutations in `lib/` or colocated `hooks/useX.ts`.
- Centralize HTTP in **`lib/api-client.ts`** (or split `admin-api.ts` / `public-api.ts` as already structured): typed responses, consistent error parsing.
- Keep components **presentational** where possible: pass data via props; avoid fetching inside deep leaf components unless isolated.

---

## 05 — Routing & code splitting

- Declare routes in `App.tsx` (or a `routes.tsx` module if it grows).
- Lazy-load heavy pages with **`React.lazy`** + **`Suspense`** (Vite-compatible). Do not use `next/dynamic`.

---

## 06 — Logging & debug (frontend only)

- **Do not** use raw `console.log` in production code paths for feature work; use a tiny **`lib/logger.ts`** that wraps `console` and **no-ops or downgrades** when `import.meta.env.PROD` is true.
- Verbose debug logging is **dev-only** — this avoids conflicting with backend `logger_setup.mdc`.

---

## 07 — Accessibility

- Semantic HTML; labels for inputs; keyboard focus for interactive elements.
- Aim for WCAG contrast on primary text and controls; test critical flows with keyboard only.

---

## 08 — Errors & boundaries

- Use **route-level or app-level `ErrorBoundary`** for render failures; show a clear recovery UI.
- Map API errors to user-visible messages (React Query `onError` / error render props).

---

## 09 — Quality gates

- Run **`npm run lint`** and **`npm run build`** in `apps/admin-dashboard` before merge.
- Add **Vitest + Testing Library** when you introduce non-trivial hooks or components worth unit testing (optional until scaffolded).

---

## 10 — Optional / future

- **shadcn/ui** or a component library: if adopted, import from the project’s `components/ui/*` barrel — not deep from `node_modules` for app code.
- **Storybook / Playwright:** add when the team commits to visual or E2E workflows; not required by this rule file today.

---

## Naming (aligned with `master.mdc`)

| Kind | Convention |
|------|----------------|
| React page/component | `PascalCase.tsx` |
| Hooks | `useThing.ts` (camelCase file name) |
| lib/utils | `kebab-case.ts` |
